---
import LabLayout from '../layouts/LabLayout.astro';
---

<LabLayout title="Manifesto">
  <section class="manifesto">
    <p class="eyebrow">Contract</p>
    <h1>Manifesto</h1>
    <p>Asymm Studio treats interface generation as a mathematical craft and bio-resonance as a privacy-bound interaction material. The project is intended to become inspectable open infrastructure, not a black-box personalization layer.</p>
    <h2>Privacy Thesis</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Math is the engine. Sacred geometry is extended, never replaced.</li>
      <li>Design DNA must be deterministic, inspectable, and region-aware.</li>
      <li>Camera frames stay inside the browser tab.</li>
      <li>Presence hashes are stored and transmitted only as one-way identity signals.</li>
      <li>Accessibility and reduced motion belong in the first pass.</li>
    </ol>
    <h2>Mathematical Foundation</h2>
    <p>The aesthetic engine derives color, type, motion, geometry, and spacing from seed quaternions on S3. The bio-resonance stack treats face stability, pulse-like optical signals, and gaze as local signals that shape UI behavior without becoming stored biometrics.</p>
    <h2>Open Intent</h2>
    <p>The lab favors small deterministic APIs, visible limitations, and source-to-target traceability. When the system simulates data, it says so; when it touches the camera, it keeps processing local and visible.</p>
    <div class="context-links">
      <a class="button-link" href="/aesthetic-engine/explorer/">Explore Seeds</a>
      <a class="button-link" href="/bio-resonance/calibration/">Inspect Calibration</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</LabLayout>
